Ad Text:
About Medcast

Medcast is a leading healthcare education provider, dedicated to advancing healthcare through innovative education solutions and products. We use cutting-edge technology to deliver exceptional learning experiences for busy clinicians and healthcare organisations. Our team embraces technology and is composed of passionate individuals who are dedicated to making a meaningful impact on healthcare. 

About the Role

Are you passionate about technology and thrive in a collaborative environment? We're seeking an experienced Chief Data Scientist to join our growing team and play a pivotal role in delivering successful technology initiatives that drive our business forward.

As our Chief Data Scientist, you’ll lead our AI and data science strategy to deliver accurate, intelligent medical education content through cutting-edge retrieval and machine learning systems.

What You'll Be Doing

Define and drive the AI/RAG technical vision and strategy in alignment with our product roadmap and business objectives
Design, build and optimize our multi-stage retrieval pipeline, including embedding selection, vector search, reranking systems, and LLM integration
Own ML system architecture decisions and set technical standards for code quality, testing, and evaluation across the AI team
Ensure medical accuracy and clinical validity by establishing evaluation criteria for medical correctness and working closely with clinical advisors
Lead model evaluation and selection for embeddings, LLMs, and rerankers, implementing A/B testing frameworks and continuous performance monitoring
Keep us at the forefront of AI innovation, researching new techniques and testing promising approaches that could benefit healthcare education
Lead and develop the AI team, creating a culture that values both innovation and rigorous quality, while partnering with senior leadership on planning and resources
Represent our work externally through research papers, open-source contributions, and speaking at industry conferences

What We're Looking For

Extensive experience in machine learning and AI, with experience in senior technical leadership roles
Deep expertise in modern AI systems, including embeddings, information retrieval, LLMs, vector databases, and building evaluation frameworks that measure what matters
Proven track record of leading AI/ML teams and shipping machine learning solutions to production at scale
Strong technical foundation in Python, PyTorch, and MLOps, with the ability to move seamlessly between strategy and hands-on problem-solving
Experience in healthcare or medical AI is highly valued, along with understanding of clinical reasoning and regulatory considerations
Research credibility through published papers or significant open-source contributions that demonstrate thought leadership in the field
Exceptional communication skills - you can explain complex technical concepts clearly to both technical and non-technical stakeholders
Natural mentor and team builder who creates environments where innovation and rigorous quality go hand in hand

Why Join Medcast?

Be part of a team that is transforming medical and healthcare education through cutting-edge technology and expert-driven content.
Work alongside passionate professionals in a dynamic and inclusive environment.
Grow your skills and experience while working close to home.

Ready to Apply?

If you're ready to drive medical AI innovation, we want to hear from you!

To apply, please submit your resume and a cover letter outlining your relevant experience and suitability for this role.

Medcast is committed to diversity, inclusion, and workplace flexibility. We welcome applications from all members of our community and strive to provide equitable access to opportunities. If you require any adjustments during the recruitment process, let us know—we're here to support you.

Senior Data Analyst

Strategic Analytics | Sydney

Are you a commercially minded data professional who thrives on turning complex data into meaningful strategic insight?

We are seeking an experienced Senior Data Analyst to provide high-level analytical expertise and evidence-based advice at a corporate level, supporting key strategic initiatives across the Education and Students Portfolio space.

This is a high-impact role where your insights will directly inform decision-making, shape institutional strategy, and improve student outcomes.

The Opportunity

In this business-critical role, you will work autonomously to deliver strategic analytics initiatives within defined timeframes. Your role will be critical role in elevating the university's data capability, day to day responsibilities will include:

Providing sophisticated data analysis and evaluation expertise at a corporate level
Delivering strategic, evidence-based insights to inform executive decision-making
Design and shape reports and dashboards that support institutional priorities
Set KPIs for analytics projects and ensure measurable outcomes
Streamline and improve data collection processes for accuracy and timeliness
Ensure the effective administration of surveys and uphold rigorous data quality standards
Resolve complex analytical challenges and provide trusted, independent advice
Identify resourcing requirements and supporting staff leadership

This is an opportunity to influence at scale, working across stakeholders in academic, operational and executive environments.

About You

You are a confident, commercially aware data professional who combines technical expertise with strategic thinking. You bring:

Significant experience in data analysis within a complex organisation (university or other education environments)
Strong capability in translating data into clear, actionable insights for senior stakeholders
Experience establishing KPIs and performance frameworks
Experience in compiling, validating and analysing data from various sources
Advanced skills in analytics tools (R, Python, SQL, Julia) and reporting platforms including SPSS software for data analysis
Advanced analytics and process design skills
Proven ability to manage survey data and ensure high data governance standards
Strong judgement, problem-solving capability and the ability to operate autonomously
Exceptional communication skills with the ability to influence at executive level

Why Join?

Play a critical role in shaping institutional strategy
Work at the intersection of data, education and student success
Influence senior leadership and drive evidence-based decision making
Be part of a forward-thinking portfolio focused on continuous improvement

If you're ready to take ownership of high-impact analytics initiatives in a strategic university environment, we'd love to hear from you.

Apply now or contact Graham Walker on 0417 630 485 to discuss details further.

The Opportunity 

Join MEGT’s IT Division as a Technical Business Analyst, reporting to the Head of IT Delivery, and play a key role in improving the efficiency and effectiveness of our organisation. 

In this role, you will partner across the organisation to proactively identify system and process optimisation opportunities, perform business analysis on projects, and support end-to-end delivery with a focus on efficient project execution and continuous improvement. You will work closely with diverse internal and external stakeholders to ensure business and customer expectations are understood and managed throughout the project lifecycle. 

Key responsibilities: 

Facilitate workshops, stakeholder interviews and process mapping sessions. 
Elicit, analyse and document business, functional and non-functional requirements. 
Translate requirements into epics, features, user stories and acceptance criteria. 
Identify impacts, dependencies, risks and constraints across systems and processes. 
Contribute to interface/API requirements, data mapping and integration specifications. 
Support UAT planning, coordination and validation against requirements. 
Liaise with staff at all levels, including Managers, Senior Managers and Executives. 
Communicate complex technical concepts in business-friendly language. 
Ensure requirements consider privacy, security and regulatory needs. 

 

About you

You are an experienced and proactive Technical Business Analyst who thrives in a collaborative environment and enjoys building positive relationships with diverse stakeholders. You bring strong analytical capability, together with the ability to engage, influence and communicate effectively across technical and non-technical stakeholders, along with: 

5+ years’ experience as a Technical Business Analyst in complex environments 
High digital literacy, including experience with Microsoft technologies such as Azure, Data Lake, SharePoint and Visio  
Experience in business analysis, business change and continuous improvement processes 
Strong communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to influence and negotiate. 
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills 
Experience working with payroll, finance/accounting and CRM systems

Drive major improvements to government financial reporting and shape future data frameworks.



Your new company

You will join a large Federal Government department delivering national programs that support Australians through evidence-informed policy and high-quality data. You will work within a high-performing team that values collaboration, strategic thinking and strong analytical capability.



Your new role

As the EL1 Financial Reporting Analyst, you will lead strategic analysis and provide expert advice on the refinement of key government financial reporting frameworks. You will review and modernise data collections and reporting definitions to ensure they capture accurate, fit-for-purpose financial information that supports evolving policy and program needs, while also improving efficiency for providers.


Working within a small, collaborative team, you will design and implement improvements to reporting structures, including the development of a multi-dimensional chart of accounts to support the flow of data through departmental systems. You will prepare high-quality briefing materials for senior executives, coordinate consultation across internal and external stakeholders, and guide the development of resources, templates and guidance materials.



This is an opportunity to influence national reporting frameworks, drive system and process improvements, and contribute to evidence-based decision-making across a major government portfolio.

What you'll need to succeed

You will bring strong technical accounting capability, expertise in financial reporting, and the ability to analyse complex financial datasets. You will hold a CPA, CA or a relevant accounting/finance qualification, with experience in regulatory, government or sector-wide reporting.


You will also demonstrate:

Deep technical accounting and financial reporting expertise.
Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills.
The ability to deliver clear, succinct analysis and advice to senior audiences.
High-level judgement, critical thinking and the ability to work under limited direction.
Strong organisational skills and attention to detail in a dynamic environment.
The ability to obtain and maintain a Baseline security clearance.


What you'll get in return

You will join a supportive, forward-thinking team committed to strengthening national financial reporting and improving data quality. The role provides the chance to influence significant reforms, work with diverse stakeholders, and contribute to programs of national importance. A competitive hourly rate is offered, along with a 12-month contract and potential extensions.



What you need to do now

If you're interested in this EL1 Financial Reporting Specialist role, please contact Alden Soe on 6112 7698 or email alden.soe@hays.com.au.

If this role isn't quite right for you, but you are seeking a new position, or if you meet most-but not all-of the requirements, I encourage you to get in touch for a confidential discussion about how your skills and experience may align with current or upcoming opportunities.

Senior Data Scientist – Credit Risk & Loss Modelling

Location: Sydney |

Salary: Up to $200k + Super + Bonus

The Role:
Join a high-growth financial services brand driving real AI and data transformation. This is production-first work, not experimentation. You’ll own credit risk, loss forecasting, and pricing models that directly influence mortgage and asset finance portfolios.
What You’ll Do
Own and productionise credit risk and loss models, including pricing and portfolio optimisation
Maintain and improve existing models, monitoring performance and retraining where needed
Work with mortgage, consumer, and commercial finance data to drive real-world outcomes
Partner with credit, risk, and product teams to embed models into daily decisioning
Optimise model performance across CoreLogic-style datasets and internal product data
Deliver actionable insights and robust BAU pipelines that impact business performance
What We’re Looking For
Proven experience in credit risk modelling, loss forecasting, or pricing
Strong skills in statistical modelling, ML, and production deployment
Experience with mortgage, consumer, or commercial lending data
Comfortable with model monitoring, retraining, and lifecycle management
Ambition to progress into a Principal Data Scientist / technical authority role
Why This Role Stands Out
Focus on real-world BAU modelling, not PoCs or theory
Direct impact on credit strategy, pricing, and portfolio performance
Exposure to enterprise AI-enabled decision systems
Clear progression to senior/principal technical leadership
Sydney Based - Hybrid

Feel free to email directly - Bendavies@preacta.com

We are seeking a highly skilled Business Analyst to support an SAP S/4HANA Public Cloud implementation. You will act as the critical link between business stakeholders and technical experts to ensure project outcomes are delivered effectively.

This role is ideal for someone who is detail‑focused, analytically strong, and comfortable operating in a fast‑paced and lean organisational environment. 10-12 month contract.

Your key responsibilities will include:

Engage with stakeholders to gather and analyse business and system requirements.

Map end‑to‑end workflows, processes, and data structures.

Prepare high‑quality documentation including Business Requirements Documents, user stories, and functional specifications.

Participate in all testing phases (functional, integration, UAT), ensuring issues are well‑documented and resolved.

Support system rollout activities including training preparation, user guides, and process documentation.

You will have:

Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication across business and technical teams.

Strong analytical and problem‑solving capability with a pragmatic, outcome‑driven approach.

Experience working within lean or small‑to‑medium‑sized organisations.

Demonstrated experience with SAP S/4HANA, preferably Public Cloud.

Four to six years’ experience as a BA on ERP implementations or upgrades.

If you are a collaborative Business Analyst with strong ERP experience and a passion for delivering high‑quality outcomes, we’d love to hear from you.

The Role

As a Data Analytics Consultant (Value Modelling), you will be responsible for building and maintaining value models that support strategic decision-making across the superannuation fund. You will work across member outcomes, investment performance, and operational efficiency - using your technical skills and domain knowledge to tell compelling stories through data.

Key Responsibilities
Design, develop and maintain value models to assess member and fund outcomes
Conduct advanced data analysis across large, complex superannuation datasets
Build and maintain interactive dashboards and visualisations using PowerBI or equivalent tools
Write clean, efficient, well-documented code in R, Python, or similar languages
Translate analytical findings into clear recommendations for non-technical stakeholders
Collaborate with client teams across actuarial, investments, member services, and finance
Contribute to the continuous improvement of modelling frameworks and data governance practices
Operate independently with minimal supervision, managing your own workload and delivery timelines

Essential
7+ years of experience in superannuation, financial services, or data analytics
Tertiary qualification in Actuarial Studies, Mathematics, Statistics, Commerce, or a related quantitative discipline
Associate or Fellow of the Institute of Actuaries (FIAA/AIAA) - strongly preferred
Strong programming skills in R, Python, or equivalent analytical languages
Demonstrated experience building and interpreting value models or financial/member outcome models
Proficiency in data visualisation tools - PowerBI, Tableau, or similar
Ability to work independently and deliver quality outputs with limited day-to-day supervision
Strong communication skills - able to present complex analytical findings to both technical and non-technical audiences

Skills & Experience
Highly Regarded
Prior experience delivering a similar value modelling capability for another superannuation fund or financial services organisation
Experience with large member administration datasets (e.g. Link, IFAA, or similar platforms)
Exposure to APRA regulatory reporting requirements in the superannuation context
Experience working in a consulting or client-facing delivery environment

Company description:



About Brisbane Catholic Education
Brisbane Catholic Education (BCE) is a vibrant learning community within the Archdiocese, employing over 12,000 people across a diverse range of positions. As the largest provider of Catholic education in Queensland, BCE is dedicated to delivering high-quality education from Prep to Year 12. Through strong partnerships with parents, governments, and the wider community, BCE fosters social responsibility, self-discipline and Catholic values in all its students. We offer a supportive working culture where care for the individual is an important part of our ethos. Arrive at work every day to a welcoming and compassionate environment, knowing that you'll be supported to take care of what's important to you. Learn more about Brisbane Catholic Education.



Job description:



Summary

As Senior Advisor Strategy, you will play a key role in shaping system‑wide priorities and decision‑making across Brisbane Catholic Education. Working closely with the Strategy Lead, you'll deliver high‑quality strategic analysis, insights and recommendations that influence policy, enterprise priorities and organisational performance. This role is ideal for a strategic thinker who enjoys tackling complex issues, working across diverse stakeholders and translating evidence into clear, practical direction.

Location: BCEO Woolloongabba
Work hours: Fulltime | Flexible Working Arrangements Available
Status: Permanent (Continuing) | Commencing March 2026
Salary: $137,560 - $152,836 plus super
Ad Close date: 09 March 2026
Contact: CareersBCE@bne.catholic.edu.au ​ 
About the opportunity

In this position you will:  

Provide high‑level strategic advice and lead initiatives that influence organisational direction, policy and practice
Analyse complex data and insights to challenge thinking, identify opportunities and support continuous improvement
Support functional teams to evaluate options and determine organisational and operational requirements
Develop strategies, frameworks and recommendations to enhance system performance and educational outcomes
Prepare high‑quality reports, briefs and committee papers on significant strategy, planning and research initiatives
Build strong relationships with internal and external stakeholders to deliver shared outcomes
Partner with BCE office and school‑based leaders to support enterprise priorities
Build capability across teams to improve effectiveness, efficiency and impact 
About you

To be successful in this position you will bring relevant contemporary skills and experience including:   

Strong experience in strategic analysis, policy development or advisory roles within complex organisations
The ability to synthesise data, research and insights into clear, evidence‑based recommendations
Well‑developed stakeholder engagement skills, with the confidence to influence and collaborate across functions
Experience preparing high‑level reports and advice for senior leaders or governance forums
A proactive, solutions‑focused mindset with the ability to manage competing priorities
Tertiary qualifications in Business Management, Economics or a related discipline (highly regarded but not essential), or equivalent experience 

Eligibility and Safeguarding requirements: 

Eligibility to work in Australia for the duration of the appointment.
Ability to obtain a National Criminal History check prior to commencement.  
Why choose BCE

Join us and be part of the largest Catholic Diocese in Queensland, nurturing your personal and professional development goals. As a valued member of our organisation, enjoy these and other rewards:

Opportunities for career advancement and professional development
Competitive remuneration and flexible work arrangements (position dependent)
Access to targeted AI tools and training with a focus on innovation and strong ethical standards. Learn more here: The Rome Call for AI Ethics and Microsoft Australia News Centre
Salary packaging and salary-sacrificing options
Active staff social club and wellness programs
Personal support for our employees and families through the Employee Assistance Program.
Fitness Passport access - discounted membership giving you flexible access to a wide network of gyms, pools and fitness facilities for you and your family.

Please note applications for this position may be considered as they are received, and an appointment made prior to the advertised close date.

Everyone at BCE models and fosters a commitment to the safeguarding of children and promotes a culture where student protection is everyone's responsibility. The Archdiocese of Brisbane has standards of conduct for workers to maintain a safe and healthy environment for children. Our commitment to these standards requires that we conduct working with children checks and background referencing for all persons who will engage in direct and regular involvement with children and young people and/or adults-at-risk. The organisation is fully committed to child safety and has a zero tolerance to abuse of children or adults-at-risk.

Equity and inclusion are at the core of our Catholic values and we recognise the benefits of a diverse workforce. We encourage and welcome candidates from all backgrounds to apply for this position.

By choosing to continue, you agree to the Privacy Policy (Employment Collection Notice which includes being contacted by Brisbane Catholic Education in future if a similar position becomes available) and to be included in BCE's talent pools for future opportunities. Show Privacy Policy

Ad Text:
Davidson is the proud recruitment partner of SEC Victoria as they accelerate Victoria's renewable energy transition.

Do work that makes a difference
The SEC is building an enterprising and dynamic team to accelerate Victoria's transition to renewables and help achieve Victoria's renewable energy target of 95% by 2035. We are working together for renewable, affordable, reliable energy for all Victorians.

SEC have an exciting and ambitious road ahead with a focus on:

Investing in renewable energy and storage projects that accelerate the transition and deliver commercial returns.
Supporting households to go all electric to reduce their emissions and energy bills.
Building the renewable energy workforce our energy transition requires.

The SEC is partnering with industry to transform the energy sector, opening the state up for further innovation and investments in renewables. This includes an initial $1 billion towards delivering 4.5 gigawatts of power through renewable energy and storage projects - the equivalent replacement capacity of coal-fired power station Loy Yang A, which is set to close in 2035.

Your role
This is a growth opportunity for an ambitious Analyst looking to accelerate their career and build deep expertise in energy spot trading. Joining the SEC's dynamic Trading team, you'll immerse yourself in a rapidly evolving energy market while contributing real value from day one. You'll work across physical markets, electricity derivatives, environmental certificate markets, and long‑term renewable offtake arrangements, giving you broad exposure to the full trading and contract management landscape.

As you develop, you'll play an increasingly active role in supporting - and eventually executing - the team's spot trading activities. This role is designed for growth, offering hands‑on learning, mentorship from experienced traders, and the chance to sharpen your analytical, commercial, and market decision‑making skills. If you're eager to grow into a trading pathway and thrive in a fast‑paced, high‑impact environment, this is the ideal next step.

The role includes occasional work outside of standard business hours to meet operational demands.

This role can be based in either SEC's Melbourne CBD office or our regional office located in Morwell.

What you will do:

Market analysis: Monitor and interpret physical, forward, and environmental markets to forecast trends and inform trading decisions, including BESS performance analysis and SEC asset back‑testing.
Reporting: Build and maintain market, position, and contract reports using SQL, Databricks, and PowerBI to support ongoing trading activities.
Spot trading: Provide spot trading coverage and real‑time operational support for SEC‑traded generation and storage assets in the NEM.
Contract management: Support management of offtake and long‑term contracts, including tracking generation availability, meeting reporting requirements, and managing contractual obligations.
Risk and compliance: Help ensure strong governance by monitoring trading activity for compliance with internal and regulatory requirements and escalating potential issues.

Who you are:
Experiences and Skills:

Must Have:

Tertiary qualifications in Mathematics, Statistics, Data Science, Engineering, Economics, Finance and/or another relevant specialisation
Solid understanding of NEM market design, pricing and wholesale electricity price drivers, with a strong desire to learn all aspects of trading and portfolio optimisation
Strong analytical, problem-solving and critical-thinking skills, with the ability to collaboratively interpret data and modelling outputs and produce and distribute meaningful insights across the organisation.
Proficiency with Databricks and programming languages (Python, R and/or SQL) to support data processing and workflow development of large time-series datasets (e.g. prices, demand, weather).
Numerical and computing skills to support the development of accessible analytical and reporting tools including Advanced Excel, PowerBI, and/or Tableau.
Excellent attention to detail and data quality discipline (validation, reconciliation and documentation)
Excellent communication skills with internal and external stakeholders and ability to clearly present on outcomes of data analysis

Highly Desirable:

At least a year of experience working in the energy industry ideally in a NEM market participant (retailer/generator/gentailer)
Knowledge of electricity derivative markets and environmental certificate markets
Exposure to long-term/structured energy purchasing agreements and offtakes

An empowered workforce
A career with SEC means you'll be joining a new and vibrant 'for purpose' government-owned renewable energy company that:

Empowers you to influence how we accelerate Victoria's renewable energy transition and decarbonise our economy.
Inspires you through meaningful, challenging work in an environment that encourages leadership and an entrepreneurial spirit.
Supports your growth through career advancement and professional development opportunities.
Provides hybrid work arrangements, with around 3 days working in Melbourne or Morwell, with flexible work options to meet individual circumstances, providing greater choice and autonomy.

How to Apply
We strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people. We are also deeply committed to building an inclusive workplace that embraces diversity and people with disability, people from the LGBTIQ community, and people from culturally diverse backgrounds. SEC strives to create a respectful and collaborative workplace culture that allows all employees to thrive.

For further information and to explore this opportunity further please contact SECRecruitment@davidsonwp.com

Please click the 'Apply Now' button. As part of the application process, you will need to provide a copy of your resume and/ or a cover letter (optional) addressing how your skills, knowledge and experience will be relevant to this role. Note: Applicants must be an Australian citizen, permanent resident or hold a valid work permit to be eligible to apply.



Please apply with current resume in Microsoft Word format only (.doc or .docx). Want to know more about Davidson? Visit us at www.davidsonwp.com

WorkCover Queensland is entering an exciting new chapter, with a renewed strategic focus and strong executive leadership guiding our organisation's 2030 Strategy. We're embarking on an enterprise-wide transformation that will enable us to continue making a positive difference to people's lives and keep Queenslanders working.

As the Manager People Analytics, you will lead the design, development and delivery of advanced data insights that drive strategic workforce decisions, lift organisational performance and strengthen employee experience. This is a critical role within our People & Strategy division, partnering closely with senior leaders across People, Finance and the broader business to ensure the right insights inform the right decisions at the right time.

You’ll combine technical capability, business acumen and strong storytelling skills to translate complex workforce data into clear, actionable insights that support workforce planning, talent strategies, performance management, organisational design and diversity and inclusion outcomes. Drawing on your leadership capability, you’ll build a high‑performing people analytics function and uplift analytical maturity across the organisation.

What You’ll Do

Lead WorkCover’s People Analytics strategy, including governance, data quality and standardisation of key workforce metrics.
Design and deliver dashboards, reports and advanced workforce analysis to support strategic business decision‑making.
Act as a trusted advisor to senior leaders, providing evidence‑based recommendations on workforce challenges and opportunities.
Oversee optimisation of people data systems, HRIS platforms and analytics tools to enhance automation and reporting efficiency.
Lead, coach and develop a specialist analytics team while building data capability across the broader People & Strategy function.

A Bit About Us

Our vision is to be the best workers’ compensation insurer, making a positive difference to people’s lives and keeping Queenslanders working. We turn care into action, act with integrity, and work together to unlock what’s possible. If you value empathy, collaboration, and continuous improvement, you’ll find a great community at WorkCover. 

Working in a collaborative team environment within a supportive and engaged organisation, you’ll enjoy a hybrid work model, access to personalised learning and development opportunities and the holistic support of our health and wellbeing program. We offer industry competitive salaries, a generous superannuation scheme (including co-contribution) and study assistance. You can find out more about our Employee Benefits by visiting Working at WorkCover Qld. 

How do I apply?

If this sounds like you, we’d love to hear from you. Submit your resume and application today! Applications close Thursday 12th March 4pm.

We are committed to ensuring WorkCover reflects the diversity of the Queensland community. We welcome applications from First Nations peoples, members of the LGBTQIA+SB community, people of all ages, people who are neurodivergent, people with disability, and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.

To ensure you have the best and most inclusive experience, please let us know if you require any reasonable adjustments or accommodations to help you confidently showcase your skills and potential. You can contact us at recruitment@workcoverqld.com.au or let our recruitment team know during your conversation with them.

Pre-employment checks will be conducted on all prospective employees. This includes a Right to Work in Australia Check, Police Check, Education Check, Reference Check, and where appropriate a Visa Check. The information provided will be treated as confidential in accordance with the Information Privacy Act 2009 (Qld).

Job Title: Category & Insights Manager - Fixed Term Contract
Ad Text:
At Saputo, we bring good to the table by making high-quality products, investing in our people, and supporting communities around the world. As a top 10 global dairy processor, we value contributions that matter and strive to foster an inclusive, growth-driven work environment. Ready to bring your best?

About the Role

We’re recruiting a Category & Insights Manager to join our Commercial Team, managing our Specialty Cheese and Food Service on a contract basis. This is a senior, high‑impact role responsible for owning category strategy, underpinned by strong consumer and category insights, and driving value creation and consumption growth within grocery retail.

This fixed‑term contract runs through to December 2026 and combines Category Management and Insights responsibilities, offering strong exposure across Sales, Marketing and Commercial teams.

Reporting to the Head of Insight & Category, the role sits at the intersection of Category Management, Sales, Marketing and Insights, operating in a fast‑paced environment with competing priorities. Success will be driven by strong commercial thinking, the ability to translate data into clear, actionable insight, and the capability to influence.

Key Responsibilities

Own category strategy and consumer insights for Specialty Cheese & Food Service, driving value and consumption growth in grocery retail

Translate complex scan, shopper panel and customer data into clear, compelling and actionable stories for Sales, Marketing, Finance and retail partners

Lead range reviews end‑to‑end, aligning internal stakeholders and delivering clear, category‑led narratives to retailers

Provide agnostic, evidence‑based category recommendations to unlock category growth

Identify and shape the innovation pipeline, from opportunity identification through concept testing and NPD input

Influence pricing, promotional and portfolio decisions through robust data and insight

Act as a key connector between Sales and Marketing, balancing priorities and managing stakeholder expectations

About You

You will bring:

Proven experience in Category Management, Insights, or a hybrid role within FMCG, retail or agency environments

Hands‑on experience with Circana / Scan / Panel data, including Coles and Woolworths customer data (required)

Strong commercial acumen, with the ability to connect insight to action and measurable outcomes

Confidence presenting to senior stakeholders and influencing decisions without direct authority

The ability to prioritise effectively in a complex, stakeholder‑driven environment

A collaborative, curious mindset, with enough conviction to drive change

What We Offer

A senior contract role with genuine visibility, accountability and commercial impact

Opportunity to influence category strategy during a period of refresh

Exposure to a high‑profile Specialty Cheese & Food Service, working closely with senior Commercial, Sales and Marketing leaders




Click “Apply for this job” to submit your application. Applicants must have full Australian working rights.

Saputo Dairy Australia is an equal opportunity employer and a proud Circle Back Initiative Employer — we commit to responding to every applicant.





As a leading dairy processor in Australia, Saputo produces, markets, and distributes a variety of products, with a portfolio of well-loved brands such as Devondale, Liddells, CHEER, Mersey Valley and Tasmanian Heritage. Our people bring these popular brands to life, while servicing our farming communities and through our AG Warehouse network.

Whether your expertise lies in manufacturing, operations, supply chain, sales, quality assurance, or in any other function, your role is integral to our success. You will make contributions that matter, all while working alongside colleagues who genuinely care about your success and who will roll up their sleeves to help.

Senior Business Analyst
Must have Trading / Equities domain experience
$180k + Super
  Role Overview:

Work with a number of stakeholders to elicit, capture and document requirements
Map current and future business processes
Identify, verify and address gaps in information provided by stakeholders, create impact assessments and gap analysis
Review design and testing deliverables to ensure completeness of requirements
Identify and drive continuous improvement opportunities
Conducting requirement workshops and document high and low level requirements and acceptance criteria’s
  Skills & Experience:

7+ years Business Analysis Experience working on transformation projects

About the RFDS

For over 95 years, the Royal Flying Doctor Service (RFDS) has been delivering the finest care to the furthest corner of Australia. We provide aeromedical emergency retrieval, primary health care, mental health and dental services to the seven million Australians who live, work and travel in rural and remote areas – often where no other health services exist.

The RFDS Federation, based in Canberra, serves as the national coordinating body for the RFDS. We manage relationships with the Commonwealth Government, build a public policy voice for better health outcomes in rural and remote Australia, and support strategic coordination across the RFDS network. Our work is guided by a commitment to improving access to high-quality health care for all Australians, no matter where they live.

About the Role

The Head of Data and Analytics will lead the development, maintenance and optimisation of the RFDS national data collection systems and data warehouse. This pivotal role ensures the organisation meets its Commonwealth reporting obligations, supports high‑quality research, and provides the insights needed for service planning and population health analysis.

You will apply advanced technical, analytical and statistical expertise across diverse RFDS systems to extract, model and interpret data relating to service delivery, patient demographics and health outcomes. Your work will directly to inform RFDS strategic planning, government policy development, and advocacy—ultimately contributing to improved health outcomes for rural and remote Australians.

Key Responsibilities

Lead all Commonwealth contract reporting across Primary Evacuation, GP/Nursing Clinics, Dental Services and Mental Health Services.

Oversee the national RFDS data warehouse, including data extraction, integration and ongoing maintenance.

Ensure data quality, consistency, confidentiality and security across all national data systems.

Provide expert advice and support to system users and contribute to software development and system enhancement initiatives.

Develop and maintain business intelligence tools and methodologies to strengthen organisational analytics capability.

Establish and manage National Minimum Data Sets (NMDS) and associated data specifications for new RFDS programs.

Conduct high‑level analysis and research on RFDS health and transport data to identify trends and inform decision‑making.

Prepare and deliver internal and external reports, publications and data outputs, including those for public release.

Lead and contribute to data‑related projects, including research into rural and remote health and demographic trends.

Drive continuous improvement in data quality and systems, including reviewing processes, developing best‑practice standards and supporting data quality initiatives

Essential qualifications, skills and experience

Tertiary qualifications in data analytics, data science or a related field 

Demonstrated experience in developing and maintaining SQL data pipelines.

Highly developed stakeholder communication and management skills.

Demonstrated experience in managing data platform environments such as Snowflake, Fabric, Databricks and Redshift.

Knowledge of data governance and cyber risk strategies

Experience in maintaining a data warehouse, modelled data and cloud based platforms

Experience using Tableau and similar data visualisation tools

Experience using Alteryx and other data extraction tools across multiple systems and databases

Highly developed research and analytical skills and ability to forecast trends and patterns from collected data.

Proven experience in interpreting data and providing advice and recommendations on appropriate courses of action.

Experience in the use of information management systems and databases.

Highly developed oral and written communications skills.

Demonstrated ability to produce clear concise and accurate assessments, reports and briefings in a range of forums.

Proven experience in problem solving and the recommendation of effective solutions.

What We Offer

Meaningful work that contributes to better health outcomes for rural and remote Australians

Generous salary packaging benefits as a not-for-profit organisation

Free staff parking and Christmas shutdown leave

The opportunity to work with a small, committed team in one of Australia's most trusted organisations

High level written and communication skills

About the Role

At Canon, our people strategy is built on insight, fairness and commercial impact. We're looking for an experienced Remuneration & Analytics Specialist to play a pivotal role in designing and delivering remuneration, incentive and analytics solutions that support our strategic goals across Canon Group Oceania.

You'll be the subject matter expert across remuneration, incentives, benefits and HR analytics. Acting as a trusted advisor, you'll bring together commercial modelling, governance, compliance and insights to support Canon's attraction, engagement and performance outcomes. You'll play a key role in the annual remuneration and incentive processes. You'll oversee superannuation governance, manage key regulatory reporting (including WGEA), and continually evolve our analytics capability to enable better decision making.

This is a highly visible role where you'll partner closely with HR, Finance and senior leaders to make a valuable contribution to the HR leadership team.

The scope of the role includes:

Lead the group‑wide remuneration review process, including commercial modelling, delivery on time and within budget
Manage annual incentive calculations and the preparation and distribution of senior leader letters
Design, review and evolve remuneration, incentive and benefits programs
Own superannuation governance, including policy management, provider relationships and committee coordination
Manage headcount governance, including weekly requests and quarterly executive reporting
Develop and enhance HR analytics dashboards and reporting in PowerBI, including performance trends and insights
Collate and manage data for WGEA reporting, tracking progress against targets
Maintain and refresh the Remuneration Governance Plan, including allowances and compliance data
Maintain SAP reporting libraries and deliver regular reporting aligned to group requirements
Proactively manage the HR P&L, tracking expenditure, reporting variances and identifying efficiency opportunities
Research market data and provide benchmarking insights and recommendations
Partner with external consultants (e.g. Mercer, Aon) to stay ahead of remuneration trends
Provide expert advice to leaders on salary, incentives, benefits and superannuation
Drive continuous improvement of remuneration processes, systems and controls
Support audits and ensure ongoing regulatory and policy compliance
Identify and oversee SAP remuneration module enhancements and upgrades

Company Description

About SEEK

SEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. Life at SEEK

SEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do. Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Places to Work in Technology (2021-2024). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.

Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. Job Description

As a Senior Strategy Manager at SEEK, you'll play a pivotal role in defining and delivering our long-term vision and growth ambitions. Focused on topics within SEEK's APAC product strategy as part of the Strategy Operations Centre of Gravity, you'll tackle some of our most critical and complex challenges, spanning multiple product and AI domains.

You'll lead deep strategic thinking, apply analytical rigour, and turn insights into action. This role suits someone who thrives in ambiguity, is energised by solving complex business problems, and is excited by the opportunity to shape SEEK's future at scale.

What You'll Be Doing

✅ Lead strategy projects spanning multiple product and AI domains, becoming the 'go-to' expert for senior leadership and the broader organisation
✅ Develop and apply analytical frameworks to investigate business issues, identify solutions and make recommendations
✅ Create situational awareness across the organisation through strategic metrics, key results, industry trends and competitor analysis
✅ Communicate strategy with simplicity and impact to all levels—from senior executives to delivery teams
✅ Collaborate in project teams alongside Product, AI and Technology stakeholders to design, test and iterate future solutions
✅ Be a vocal advocate for the strategy, providing guidance to execution teams to ensure alignment

The Opportunity

You'll join SEEK's global Strategy team, a high-performing group of ~40 ex-consultants from premier firms, working across APAC.  With exposure to some of SEEK's most senior leaders, including the Head of Strategy Operations, Directors of Strategy, and Group Executives of Product, AI and Technology, you'll have a rare opportunity to shape the long-term direction of one of the region's most recognised tech brands. Our team culture is caring, curious and impact-oriented, and we're united by a shared purpose: helping people live more fulfilling and productive working lives.

Qualifications

✔ 5-8 years' experience in strategy-related roles, with 3-4 years in a top-tier strategy consulting firm
✔ Highly developed conceptual reasoning, analytical and problem-solving skills with proven ability to frame strategic problems
✔ Experience in developing business-level strategy and breaking this down into objectives, targets and initiatives
✔ Track record of delivering results through cross-functional teams
✔ Ability to influence and build support for fact-based recommendations with diverse stakeholders
✔ High learning orientation and desire to become a global expert in online marketplace design and operations
✔ Passion for growth strategy and excellent business acumen, with experience leading complex and ambiguous strategic projects
✔ Experience in media, internet or tech industries is a plus

Additional Information

At SEEK we offer:

Annual Performance Bonus Plan
Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.
Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave
Support for parents with 14 weeks paid primary carers leave and 2 weeks paid leave for partners
The opportunity to work from anywhere for up to 4 weeks per financial year
Free income protection insurance

Evaluate integration of custodial interventions with community-based throughcare models.

Conduct comprehensive reviews of DFV, violent and sexual offending research.
Synthesise trauma-informed and evidence-based methodologies.
Identify emerging trends in perpetrator intervention and victim-survivor safety.
Highlight evidence gaps, particularly for high-risk cohorts in secure environments.

Job Title: Senior Financial Planning & Analysis Business Partner
Ad Text:
Location - Sydney or Brisbane, Australia
Work Arrangement - Hybrid




The Senior FP&A Business Partner is a critical role within the FP&A CoE, providing end‑to‑end financial planning, consolidation, and performance insight to support effective decision‑making across the business. The role plays a central part in end‑of‑month performance management, budgeting, forecasting, and long‑range planning, pulling together financial results, operational inputs, and key drivers into a coherent, decision‑ready view for senior leadership. The role partners closely with various areas across the business to ensure alignment between actual performance, forecasts, and strategic plans. 




The role plays a critical part in driving performance excellence, leveraging continuous improvement (LEAN) principles, SAP S/4HANA, automation, and effective change management to improve recovery accuracy, reduce leakage, and enhance end‑to‑end process efficiency. The role also works closely with offshore shared service centres to standardise processes, improve data quality, and enable scalable, efficient operations.







What we do at Weir
We are a global leader in mining technology for a sustainable future. We help our customers extract the resources the world needs more efficiently and more sustainably. Our planet’s future depends on the transition to renewable energy, and that transition can only happen with the metals and minerals our customers deliver. So, we work side by side with mines across the globe to move less rock, use less energy, use water wisely, and create less waste. Together, we drive the shift to smart, efficient, and more sustainable mining.




Make your impact
You’ll play a key role in solving real-world challenges. You’ll apply your skills to deliver results that matter whether that’s through engineering, planning or customer support. You’ll work with purpose, learn every day and help shape a more sustainable future.







What you’ll do

Performance Management: Own and coordinate the FP&A contribution to month-end close, consolidating financial results, flash reporting, and performance analysis to provide a clear, decision-ready view for senior leadership.

Business Partnering: Act as a trusted FP&A partner to senior business and finance stakeholders, with a strong focus on business partnering to ensure alignment between actual performance, forecasts, and strategic plans.

Budgeting & Forecasting: Lead the coordination and consolidation of budgets, forecasts, and long-range plans, developing driver-based models linking operational activity to financial outcomes, challenging assumptions to ensure robust and transparent plans.

Reporting & Insights: Provide clear, decision-oriented insights by translating financial results, forecasts, and trends into actionable narratives; review and improve management and executive reporting for relevance and alignment with key value drivers.

Continuous Improvement: Apply LEAN principles and automation to streamline FP&A processes, improve recovery accuracy, reduce leakage, and enhance end-to-end process efficiency.

Systems & Governance: Serve as a key FP&A SME for planning and reporting tools including SAP S/4HANA; ensure strong data governance, reconciliation, and control across planning and reporting cycles.

Safety First: Demonstrate 100% commitment to our zero harm behaviors in support of our drive towards developing a world-class safety culture.







What you’ll bring


Must-haves:

Bachelor’s degree in finance, accounting, economics, or business

Strong experience in FP&A, financial planning, or management reporting in a complex environment

Proven expertise in budgeting, forecasting, consolidation, and performance analysis

Strong working knowledge of SAP S/4HANA and FP&A/reporting tools




Nice-to-haves:




Professional qualification (CA, CPA, or CIMA)

Experience applying continuous improvement (LEAN) and automation in finance processes

Excellent communication and storytelling skills

Ability to influence senior stakeholders and operate effectively in a matrix environment







Why join Weir?


We live our values we think safety first, do the right thing, respect each other, aim high, and delight our customers. We encourage our people to lead by example and celebrate our successes.


We’re passionate about our purpose to help deliver the natural resources that are essential to create a better future for the world. We do this by combining our deep customer insights, world-class engineering, materials science expertise, and intelligent automation to deliver innovative end-to-end solutions incorporating our signature technologies.


We believe your voice matters and your ideas make a difference. We’re working hard to nurture a diverse culture where our people feel like they belong and can do the best work of their lives. You can help shape our unique culture through our inclusion networks and safety initiatives.







Benefits

Competitive pay

Career development and learning support

Access to global inclusion networks

Regional and team-specific benefits

Sharebuilder scheme

Wellness support for you and your family

Collaboration with global teams

Study support
